# VCS Provider Configuration Example
#
# This file demonstrates how to configure the workflow system to use
# different VCS providers (GitHub or Azure DevOps).
#
# Copy this file to .vcs_config.yaml and uncomment the section you need.

# ==============================================================================
# Option 1: GitHub (Default)
# ==============================================================================
# If you're using GitHub, no configuration file is needed!
# The system auto-detects GitHub from your git remote URL.
#
# However, you can explicitly configure it:
#
# vcs_provider: github

# ==============================================================================
# Option 2: Azure DevOps
# ==============================================================================
# Azure DevOps requires explicit configuration with organization and project.
#
# Uncomment and configure the following:

# vcs_provider: azure_devops
#
# azure_devops:
#   # Organization URL (with https://)
#   organization: "https://dev.azure.com/myorg"
#
#   # Project name
#   project: "MyProject"

# ==============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ==============================================================================
#
# GitHub Setup:
# 1. Install GitHub CLI: https://cli.github.com/
# 2. Authenticate: gh auth login
# 3. No configuration file needed (auto-detected)
#
# Azure DevOps Setup:
# 1. Install Azure CLI: https://learn.microsoft.com/cli/azure/
# 2. Install Azure DevOps extension: az extension add --name azure-devops
# 3. Authenticate: az login
# 4. Copy this file to .vcs_config.yaml
# 5. Uncomment and configure the azure_devops section above
# 6. Set defaults: az devops configure --defaults organization=https://dev.azure.com/myorg project=MyProject
#
# ==============================================================================
# How Detection Works
# ==============================================================================
#
# The VCS adapter uses this detection order:
# 1. Load .vcs_config.yaml (if exists) → use specified provider
# 2. Detect from git remote URL
#    - github.com → GitHub
#    - dev.azure.com → Azure DevOps
#    - visualstudio.com → Azure DevOps
# 3. Default to GitHub (backward compatibility)
#
# ==============================================================================
# Validation
# ==============================================================================
#
# Test your configuration:
#   python .claude/skills/git-workflow-manager/scripts/create_worktree.py feature test-vcs contrib/yourname
#
# The script will attempt to get your VCS username and report any errors.
